As the festive season draws close, criminals are looking to make up their Christmas shopping list and on Sunday a heavily armed gang struck at a jewellery store in Gateway and made off merchandise and cash. Colonel Thembeka Mbele, KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson said that a group of heavily armed men entered the jewellery store at a shopping mall and made off with an undisclosed amount of cash and jewellery. “No shots were fired and no injuries have been reported. A case of business robbery was opened at Durban North police station for investigation,” Mbele said.